.TH "bd70528_wdt_set" 9 "bd70528_wdt_set" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
bd70528_wdt_set \- arm or disarm watchdog timer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" bd70528_wdt_set
.BI "(struct rohm_regmap_dev *data "  ","
.BI "int enable "  ","
.BI "int *old_state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "data" 12
device data for the PMIC instance we want to operate on
.IP "enable" 12
new state of WDT. zero to disable, non zero to enable
.IP "old_state" 12
previous state of WDT will be filled here
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Arm or disarm WDT on BD70528 PMIC. Expected to be called only by
BD70528 RTC and BD70528 WDT drivers. The rtc_timer_lock must be taken
by calling bd70528_wdt_lock before calling bd70528_wdt_set.
